<TITLE>Alien and Harry Potter Actor John Hurt Dies</TITLE>
<TEXT>
John Hurt whose acting career spanned five and a half decades has died He was 77 Hurt was featured in three Harry Potter films as wandmaker Garrick Ollivander and was also known for his roles in Alien Hellboy and dozens of other films and television programs His role in Midnight Express earned him an Academy Award nomination for Best Supporting Actor in 1978 and in 1980 he was again nominated for an Oscar this time for Best Actor for his role in David Lynch s The Elephant Man John Hurt as the War Doctor in Doctor Who Hurt s appearances over the years read like a who s who list of memorable sci fi and fantasy movies and television shows In Alien he played Kane the first of the crew to die and the first ever Alien chestburster victim in arguably one of the most famous scenes in movie history and he also lent his voice to the 1978 animated version of The Lord of the Rings as Aragorn and voiced the Horned King in Disney s The Black Cauldron He also appeared in V for Vendetta Snowpiercer Indiana Jones and the Kingdom of the Crystal Skull and Spaceballs parodying his famous Alien role and can currently be seen in theaters opposite Natalie Portman in Jackie In recent years he also played the War Doctor in Doctor Who In the movie adaptation of George Orwell s 1984 Hurt took on the role of Winston Smith the protagonist and employee of the Ministry of Truth Hurt is survived by his wife Anwen Rees Myers and two sons Alexander and Nicholas Seth Macy is IGN s weekend web producer and just wants to be your friend Follow him on Twitter sethmacy or subscribe to Seth Macy s YouTube channel 
